            "text/plain": "2b passed! lengths = [3, 8, 2, 7]\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 6
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-2c",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 2c — `sorted`\n\nThe pipeline collects words, but they should come out **sorted alphabetically**.\nAdd one intermediate operation to sort them.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-2c"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-2c",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<String> words = List.of(\"mango\", \"apple\", \"fig\", \"cherry\");\n\nList<String> sorted = words.stream()\n    .sorted()\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert sorted.equals(List.of(\"apple\", \"cherry\", \"fig\", \"mango\"))\n    : \"Expected alphabetical order but got \" + sorted;\nSystem.out.println(\"2c passed! sorted = \" + sorted);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-2c",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 7,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "2c passed! sorted = [apple, cherry, fig, mango]\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 7
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-2d",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 2d — `reduce`\n\nSum all the integers in the list using `reduce`. The identity value (starting value) is `0`.\n\nHint: `Integer::sum` is a method reference with a compatible signature.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-2d"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-2d",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\n\nList<Integer> nums = List.of(4, 7, 2, 9, 1);\n\nint total = nums.stream()\n    .reduce(0, Integer::sum);\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert total == 23 : \"Expected 23 but got \" + total;\nSystem.out.println(\"2d passed! total = \" + total);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-2d",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 9,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 9,
      "outputs": [
