          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "2d passed! total = 23\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 9
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-2e",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 2e — Method reference\n\nThe pipeline currently uses a lambda `s -> s.toUpperCase()`. \nReplace it with an equivalent **method reference**.\n\nThe output should be identical.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-2e"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-2e",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<String> words = List.of(\"hello\", \"world\", \"java\");\n\nList<String> upper = words.stream()\n    .map(String::toUpperCase)  // replace this lambda with a method reference\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert upper.equals(List.of(\"HELLO\", \"WORLD\", \"JAVA\")) : \"Got \" + upper;\nSystem.out.println(\"2e passed! upper = \" + upper);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-2e",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 10,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "2e passed! upper = [HELLO, WORLD, JAVA]\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 10
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-2f",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 2f — `distinct` + `sorted`\n\nThe list contains duplicates. Produce a list of **unique** values in **ascending order**.\n\nAdd the two missing intermediate operations (in the right order!).",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-2f"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-2f",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<Integer> nums = List.of(5, 3, 5, 1, 3, 2, 1, 4);\n\nList<Integer> result = nums.stream()\n    .distinct()\n    .sorted()\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert result.equals(List.of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)) : \"Expected [1,2,3,4,5] but got \" + result;\nSystem.out.println(\"2f passed! result = \" + result);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-2f",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 11,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "2f passed! result = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 11
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-2g",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 2g — Custom `Comparator` with a lambda\n\nSort the list of words **by length** (shortest first) using `Collections.sort` and a lambda comparator.\n\nFill in the lambda where indicated.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-2g"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-2g",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\n\nList<String> words = new ArrayList<>(List.of(\"banana\", \"fig\", \"kiwi\", \"plum\", \"strawberry\"));\n\nCollections.sort(words, (a, b) -> Integer.compare(a.length(), b.length()));\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\n// just check first and last; middle may vary for equal-length words\nassert words.get(0).equals(\"fig\")        : \"Shortest word should be first, got \" + words.get(0);\nassert words.get(4).equals(\"strawberry\") : \"Longest word should be last, got \" + words.get(4);\nSystem.out.println(\"2g passed! words = \" + words);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-2g",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 13,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 13,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "2g passed! words = [fig, kiwi, plum, banana, strawberry]\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 13
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-part3",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "---\n## Part 3 — Build a Full Pipeline\n\nNow you write the entire stream expression. The setup code and assertions are provided; everything in between is up to you.\n\nThink about which operations you need, and in what order.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-part3"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "md-3a",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 3a — Filter, map, collect\n\nGiven a list of integers, produce a list containing **only the even numbers, each multiplied by 3**.\n\nExample: `[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]` → `[6, 12, 18]`",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-3a"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-3a",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<Integer> nums = List.of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6);\n\nList<Integer> result = nums.stream()\n    .filter(n -> n % 2 == 0)\n    .map(n -> n * 3)\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert result.equals(List.of(6, 12, 18)) : \"Expected [6, 12, 18] but got \" + result;\nSystem.out.println(\"3a passed! result = \" + result);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-3a",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 14,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "3a passed! result = [6, 12, 18]\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 14
