    {
      "id": "md-3b",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 3b — Map to different type, filter, reduce\n\nThis exercise mirrors the lecture's `pipe7Test` example.\n\nGiven the array `{\"b3\", \"b7\", \"b1\", \"b9\", \"b4\"}`, write a pipeline that:\n1. Strips the leading `\"b\"` from each string\n2. Parses each remaining string as an `int`\n3. Keeps only values **strictly less than 5**\n4. Returns their **sum** using `reduce`\n\nExpected result: `3 + 1 + 4 = 8`",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-3b"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-3b",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.Arrays;\n\nString[] data = {\"b3\", \"b7\", \"b1\", \"b9\", \"b4\"};\n\nint result = Arrays.stream(data)\n    .map(s -> s.substring(1))\n    .mapToInt(Integer::parseInt)\n    .filter(n -> n < 5)\n    .reduce(0, Integer::sum);\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert result == 8 : \"Expected 8 but got \" + result;\nSystem.out.println(\"3b passed! result = \" + result);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-3b",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 15,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 15,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "3b passed! result = 8\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 15
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-3c",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 3c — Working with strings end-to-end\n\nGiven a list of words, build a pipeline that:\n1. Removes any word shorter than 4 characters\n2. Converts surviving words to uppercase\n3. Sorts them alphabetically\n4. Collects into a `List<String>`\n\nInput: `[\"the\", \"quick\", \"brown\", \"fox\", \"jumps\", \"over\"]`  \nExpected: `[\"BROWN\", \"JUMPS\", \"OVER\", \"QUICK\"]`",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-3c"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-3c",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<String> words = List.of(\"the\", \"quick\", \"brown\", \"fox\", \"jumps\", \"over\");\n\nList<String> result = words.stream()\n    .filter(w -> w.length() >= 4)\n    .map(String::toUpperCase)\n    .sorted()\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert result.equals(List.of(\"BROWN\", \"JUMPS\", \"OVER\", \"QUICK\"))\n    : \"Expected [BROWN, JUMPS, OVER, QUICK] but got \" + result;\nSystem.out.println(\"3c passed! result = \" + result);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-3c",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 16,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 16,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "3c passed! result = [BROWN, JUMPS, OVER, QUICK]\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 16
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-3d",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 3d — `collect` to a different form: joining strings\n\nYou can collect into things other than a list. `Collectors.joining(delimiter)` is a terminal collector that concatenates all stream elements into one `String`.\n\n**Task:** From the list of names below, build a pipeline that:\n1. Filters out all names that don't start with `\"A\"`\n2. Sorts alphabetically\n3. Collects them into a single comma-separated string, meaning `\",\"` is the delimiter\n\nExpected result: `\"Alice,Anna,Arthur\"`",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-3d"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-3d",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<String> names = List.of(\"Bob\", \"Anna\", \"Alice\", \"Charlie\", \"Arthur\", \"Amy\", \"Diana\");\n\nString result = names.stream()\n    .filter(s -> s.startsWith(\"A\"))\n    .sorted()\n    .collect(Collectors.joining(\",\"));\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\n// Note: Amy is < 4 chars — check the filter condition carefully!\n// Hint: the expected string has exactly three names.\nassert result.equals(\"Alice,Anna,Arthur\") : \"Expected 'Alice,Anna,Arthur' but got '\" + result + \"'\";\nSystem.out.println(\"3d passed! result = \\\"\" + result + \"\\\"\");",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-3d",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 19,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 19,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "3d passed! result = \"Alice,Amy,Anna,Arthur\"\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 19
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-3e",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 3e — Finding a maximum with a lambda comparator\n\n`Stream.max(Comparator)` finds the largest element in the stream according to the given comparator, but doesn't return the value directly — it wraps it in an `Optional<T>`. To get the actual value out, chain `.get()` onto the end of your pipeline.\n\n**Task:** From the list of words, find the **longest** word.\n\nExpected: `\"strawberry\"`",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-3e"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-3e",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<String> words = List.of(\"fig\", \"strawberry\", \"plum\", \"kiwi\", \"apricot\");\n\nString longest = words.stream()\n    .max((a, b) -> Integer.compare(a.length(), b.length()))\n    .get();\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert longest.equals(\"strawberry\") : \"Expected 'strawberry' but got '\" + longest + \"'\";\nSystem.out.println(\"3e passed! longest = \" + longest);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-3e",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 20,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 20,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "3e passed! longest = strawberry\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 20
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "md-3f",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 3f ⭐ — Challenge: multi-step transformation\n\nThis is the most complex exercise. Take your time.\n\nYou are given a list of CSV-style strings, each representing a student's name and score:\n```\n[\"Alice:82\", \"Bob:91\", \"Clara:58\", \"David:74\", \"Eva:91\", \"Frank:63\"]\n```\n\nWrite a pipeline that:\n1. Splits each string on `\":\"` to get the score part\n2. Parses the score as an `int`\n3. Keeps only scores **≥ 70**\n4. Returns the **average** of those scores as a `double`\n\nPassing scores: 82, 91, 74, 91 → average = `(82+91+74+91)/4 = 84.5`\n\nHints:\n- `\"Alice:82\".split(\":\")[1]` gives `\"82\"`\n- Use `mapToInt(...)` instead of `map(...)` for the parsing step — unlike `map`, `mapToInt` converts the stream to an `IntStream`, which gives you access to numeric operations like `average()`\n- `average()` returns an `OptionalDouble` — call `.getAsDouble()` to retrieve it.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "md-3f"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-3f",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<String> records = List.of(\n    \"Alice:82\", \"Bob:91\", \"Clara:58\", \"David:74\", \"Eva:91\", \"Frank:63\"\n);\n\ndouble avg = records.stream()\n    .map(s -> s.split(\":\")[1])\n    .mapToInt(Integer::parseInt)\n    .filter(score -> score >= 70)\n    .average()\n    .getAsDouble();\n\n// --- do not edit below ---\nassert avg == 84.5 : \"Expected 84.5 but got \" + avg;\nSystem.out.println(\"3f passed! average passing score = \" + avg);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "code-3f",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 21,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 21,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "3f passed! average passing score = 84.5\r\n"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 21
        }
      ]
    },
